Improved Grab	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:FeralTemplateTrait.SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.Improved Grab	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:If a feral creature hits an opponent that is at least one size category smaller than itself with a Rake attack, it deals normal damage and attempts to start a grapple as a free action without provoking an attack of opportunity. If it gets a hold, it can rake if it has that ability (see below). Alternatively, it has the option to conduct the grapple normally, or simply use its Rake to hold the opponent (-20 penalty on grapple check, but the feral creature is not considered grappled). In either case, each successful grapple check it makes during successive rounds automatically deals Rake damage. See the Monster Manual for additional rules.	KEY:Feral ~ Improved Grab																											SOURCEPAGE:SS30
