Loom	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:GhostBruteTemplateTrait.GhostBruteSpecialAttack.SpecialAttack.Supernatural	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A ghost brute can make itself more intimidating by exaggerating its natural size. It can appear up to two sizes larger than normal for 10 minutes each day, which need not be continuous. This enlargement is illusory; the creature's attack bonus and Armor Class remain unchanged. However, the ghost brute gains a +4 circumstance bonus on Bluff and Intimidate checks while Enlarged.	KEY:Ghost Brute ~ Loom																											SOURCEPAGE:SS30
Slavering Doom	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:GhostBruteTemplateTrait.GhostBruteSpecialAttack.SpecialAttack.Supernatural	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A ghost brute's jaws drip with a glowing ectoplasmic drool that exists in both ethereal and corporeal form. The ectoplasm dissipates on contact with nonliving material, but if it touches a living being, that opponent must make a successful Fortitude save (DC %1) or take 1d6 points of negative energy damage. The drool can be delivered through a bite attack against an ethereal opponent, or a melee touch attack against an opponent on the Material Plane. Alternatively, the drool can simply be sprayed onto a nearby creature as a ranged touch attack.|GhostBruteAbilityDC	KEY:Ghost Brute ~ Slavering Doom																											SOURCEPAGE:SS30
