Mummy Rot	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:MummifiedTemplateTrait.SpecialAttack.Supernatural	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Any creature hit by any of a mummified creature's natural weapons must succeed on a Fortitude save (DC %1) or contract mummy rot. The incubation period is 1 day, and the disease deals 1d6 points of Constitution damage. Because it is a supernatural disease, mummy rot continues until the victim reaches Constitution 0 (and dies) or receives a remove disease spell or similar magic (see Disease in Chapter 3 of the DUNGEON MASTER's Guide). An afflicted creature that dies shrivels away into sand and dust, blowing away into nothing at the first wind, unless both remove disease and raise dead are cast on the remains within 6 rounds.|MummyRotDC	KEY:Mummified ~ Mummy Rot				DEFINE:MummyRotDC|0					BONUS:VAR|MummyRotDC|DefaultDCCha	BONUS:VAR|MummyRotDC|2|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Ability Focus (Mummy Rot)								ABILITY:Ability Focus|AUTOMATIC|Mummy Rot									SOURCEPAGE:SS30
