Detach	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SymbioticTemplateTrait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:If the survival of a symbiotic creature is threatened, its two members can separate in an effort to save at least one of them (often this is the guest). This process deals 1d6 points of damage to the host. Detaching is a standard action that provokes an attack of opportunity, which may be made against host or guest. A symbiotic creature may also separate to better bring to bear a host's or guest's special attacks. Reengaging is not a simple matter; it takes one day of complete rest. If the reattaching creatures are disturbed during this process, each takes 1d6 points of Constitution damage from bleeding, and they remain separate.	KEY:Symbiotic ~ Detach																											SOURCEPAGE:SS30
